<br>
  I don't understand your point of view actually. <br>
<br>
  Yes if pets were beta neutral, than yes they could chase a fleeing mob (as would some players), help kill said mob and return with no train in tow.<br>
<br>
  A lot of people forget a fleeing mob WILL bring back friends if it is not killed, so people will chase it, as will a pet. <br>
<br>
  Why is it, if the pet chases it, with the rest, that it is the pet that will run back to it's guard point, AND not care if a mob is in the way, it runs right past it, and train to camp begins (some players do this also, but the good ones, will see said mob, and detour around it. A pet can't detour, it follows preset pathing). I know I will hear again, that is part of pet control.. etc.. Yes I know that as well, and after 60 levels it is getting OLD. I want my pet to attack ONLY what I tell it to, Never to switch a target unless I tell it to, or at least GATE back to it's guard position after the mob it is told to attack dies.<br>
<br>
  Summon companion was put into the game because Verant realized that pathing is not the fault of the players, and they admit there is little they can do to fix it.<br>
<br>
  That doesn't alter the fact that in some raids or certain zones, I can make a pet, and sick it on a mob 2 feet away, and the pet starts running away from the mob, loops around and heads back, this causes trains as we all know. <br>
<br>
  I don't want to hear about pet control in that situation, what kind of control is just killing off your pet. It just shows you ran a Earthen Boot quest. I sick pet, it zooms off the wrong way. Click boots. Wow 60 levels to learn that? Nope run the quest as soon as you can, because job one of a magician is to KILL their own pets when pathing makes them a liability. <br>
<br>
  Great pet control, I know how to click earthen boots. Sorry, that just made a pet in that place unusable where you just set up camp. So me playing my magician, just became 1/2 as useful as I was. <br>
<br>
  Also if this is your 1st trip to that dungeon or zone with that bad of pathing, you have no idea what will happen, the 1st time you sick ole Goner on a mob 2 or 3 feet away. If it heads right too it, great. If it loops a little, but not too far. OK I can deal with that. If it loops a larger radius, where mobs may spawn, or wander it is a liability, and I don't want to kill off a pet, for no fault of my own, but do to game mechanics.<br>
<br>
Calebe<br>
